<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>About - Movie Rental</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
    }
    .about-header {
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #0d6efd, #6610f2);
      color: white;
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 0 0 1rem 1rem;
    }
    .tech-card {
      transition: transform 0.2s;
    }
    .tech-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-5px);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="about-header text-center mb-5">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">About Our Movie Rental System</h1>
      <p class="lead">Built with modern web technologies and deployed with scalability in mind.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="container mb-5">
    <div class="row g-5">
      <!-- Sidebar Navigation -->
      <!-- <aside class="col-md-3">
        <div class="list-group shadow-sm">
          <a href="/" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Home</a>
          <a href="/films" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Movies</a>
          <a href="/rentals" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Rentals</a>
          <a href="/customers" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">Customers</a>
          <a href="/about" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action active">About</a>
        </div>
      </aside> -->

      <!-- About Content -->
      <section class="col-md-9">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          This application is a movie rental system developed with <strong>Node.js</strong> and <strong>Express.js</strong>.
          It demonstrates full-stack development with a focus on CRUD functionality, authentication, and a clean, responsive UI.
        </p>
        <p>
          The project is deployed using modern CI/CD pipelines, ensuring reliability and scalability for production use.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Technologies Used</h2>
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 g-4">
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Backend</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>Node.js</li>
                  <li>Express.js</li>
                  <li>REST API structure</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Frontend</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>EJS templating engine</li>
                  <li>Bootstrap 5 for styling</li>
                  <li>Custom JS and validation</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Database</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>MySQL (Sakila schema)</li>
                  <li>Data access layer with repositories</li>
                  <li>Staff & customer session handling</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Deployment</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>CI/CD with GitHub Actions</li>
                  <li>Hosted on with Docker</li>
                  <li>Reverse proxy via Nginx</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Features by Version</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>v1</strong> – Basic movie listings</li>
          <li><strong>v2</strong> – Add movie form, improved styling, CI/CD setup</li>
          <li><strong>v3</strong> – Add register and login forms. backend database</li>
          <li><strong>v4</strong> – Better error handling, validation, Bootstrap styling</li>
          <li><strong>v5</strong> – Customer & staff management features, documentation</li>
          <li><strong>v6</strong> – Authentication for staff/customers, CRUD rental tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Future Development</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Rental views access history</li>
          <li>Search functionality for movies & customers</li>
          <li>Late fee & due date system</li>
          <li>Public REST API</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Source Code</h2>
        <p>
          The project source code is available on GitHub:  
          <a href="https://github.com/s-kroonen/POC-Avans-KeuzeKompas" target="_blank">https://github.com/s-kroonen/POC-Avans-KeuzeKompas</a>
        </p>

        <% if (user && user.is_admin) { %>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
            <strong>Admin Access:</strong> You are logged in as a staff member.  
            <a href="/admin" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary ms-2">Go to Admin Panel</a>
          </div>
        <% } %>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

</body>
</html>
